definitions.definition: ( video games , slang ) Used to trash-talk an opposing team at the end of a game by pointing out a skill difference between some role and the same role on the other team.
examples: tank diff (i.e., the deciding factor in the game was the difference in skill between the teams' tank players)

definitions.definition: ( computing ) Any program which compares two files or sets of files and outputs a description of the differences between them.
( computing ) The output of a diff program, a diff file .
( automotive ) Abbreviation of differential : the differential gear in an automobile.
examples: This diff is capable of locking up when wheel slip occurs.

definitions.definition: ( medicine ) Abbreviation of differential : differential of types of white blood cell in a complete blood count .
